Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:02.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Them!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.97,0:00:04.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oracion Seis!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.51,0:00:05.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.92,0:00:08.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't they seem really different?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.75,0:00:10.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the members \Nare different, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.49,0:00:14.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, three in a row!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.90,0:00:16.69,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Oracion Seis-Oracion Seis-Oracion Seis
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.65,0:00:17.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It really is Oracion Seis!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.00,0:00:18.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.66,0:00:22.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The reborn Oracion Seis! I'm very \Nglad to make your acquaintance!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.20,0:00:24.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Reborn Oracion Seis?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.95,0:02:07.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.53,0:02:10.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the reborn Oracion Seis.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.74,0:02:12.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Midnight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.79,0:02:14.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That name belongs to the distant past.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.63,0:02:18.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please remember me henceforth as Brain II.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:22.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talkin' about, "the second"?! \NYou bastards just come strollin' in...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.16,0:02:23.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.60,0:02:26.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have just one wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.87,0:02:29.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To carry out my father's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.65,0:02:33.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To destroy everything that has a form...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.15,0:02:35.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still talking that nonsense?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.28,0:02:40.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Legion, Fairy Tail...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.41,0:02:43.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mission is now over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.59,0:02:46.97,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Oracion Seis
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.97,0:02:48.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the devil is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.81,0:02:51.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan! Don't let them get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.20,0:02:52.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:56.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kiddin'! That's our line!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.61,0:02:57.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.09,0:03:02.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Reborn Oracion Seis Appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.70,0:03:07.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The maggots are swarming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.74,0:03:13.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll knock that right back to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.92,0:03:21.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That shield didn't repel it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.70,0:03:24.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy-rin, I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.83,0:03:27.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cling to me in the \Nmiddle of the confusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.35,0:03:28.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Back off!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.46,0:03:29.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.27,0:03:31.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To me, all forms of magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.10,0:03:36.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to his magic nullifying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.53,0:03:37.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.85,0:03:43.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It refracted the range of Byro-san's \Nmagic and attacked simultaneously!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.78,0:03:45.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he's called Brain-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.73,0:03:47.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Carla! Do you feel it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.77,0:03:51.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Extraordinary, menacing magic power...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:55.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ownership of the Infinity Clock \Nis determined by the wizard
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.68,0:03:57.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that carves his seal upon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.00,0:04:00.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, just now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.37,0:04:04.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,this clock has become our property.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.37,0:04:14.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pleasant sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.47,0:04:19.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Suddenly coming out of nowhere \Nand snatching it away is cowardly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.55,0:04:23.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear your indignation...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.80,0:04:25.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're all in a state of confusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.48,0:04:28.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's laughable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.17,0:04:33.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,People of the darkness like us aren't \Neven permitted to touch this clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.83,0:04:36.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why we gathered you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.50,0:04:39.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was our plot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.64,0:04:41.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.95,0:04:43.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We were used...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.19,0:04:45.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.65,0:04:49.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why on earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.85,0:04:53.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...did my father...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.69,0:04:57.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A chill just ran up my spine! \NThese guys are scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.76,0:05:00.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The magic I'm feeling coming off of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.01,0:05:02.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's in a different league \Nthan what they had before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.06,0:05:03.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who gives a damn?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.78,0:05:06.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You danced in the palm of our hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.98,0:05:08.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.58,0:05:11.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.40,0:05:15.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu's fire was dispersed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.64,0:05:16.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:17.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Wind Magic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.79,0:05:21.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wind... Nothing as gentle as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.29,0:05:26.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a storm. A storm is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.52,0:05:30.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that face, that voice... Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.50,0:05:31.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.76,0:05:35.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw right through him! This \Nman was formerly in Eisenwald!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:39.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He is most definitely... Erigor-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.15,0:05:41.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Grim Reaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.65,0:05:43.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erigor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.12,0:05:44.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.20,0:05:45.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You... that form...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.19,0:05:48.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,People sure do change, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.60,0:05:52.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever! Come down here so I \Ncan beat the crap outta you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.25,0:05:56.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Brain, how long are we \Ngoing to waste time here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.03,0:05:58.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a grand aim, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.27,0:06:00.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.95,0:06:03.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's Fairy Tail...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:06.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't forget the humiliation \Nfrom seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.77,0:06:10.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Play with them a bit. Cobra, Racer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.45,0:06:11.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.13,0:06:13.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:14.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Engage!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:15.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:22.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that just now?! \NI couldn't see anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.57,0:06:24.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.54,0:06:27.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like another person altogether, \Nin both speed and power!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.69,0:06:28.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to his Slow Magic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:31.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he's using it here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.69,0:06:35.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's like a beast... A wild \Nanimal that's after its prey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.74,0:06:37.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:42.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, shrine \Nmaiden of the sky... and cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.35,0:06:46.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to ask you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.02,0:06:50.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What, you don't know the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.94,0:06:52.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then begone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:54.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.01,0:06:55.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this overpowering feeling?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.81,0:06:57.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Cobra!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.90,0:07:01.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your opponent is me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:03.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.83,0:07:06.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As always, your voice is abrasive!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.73,0:07:09.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...is me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.31,0:07:15.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Michelle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.11,0:07:16.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll live...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.82,0:07:18.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.47,0:07:22.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound became an incredible \Nwall of pressure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.07,0:07:25.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Cobra... You bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.85,0:07:29.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear your despair...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.27,0:07:32.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be destroyed by your own voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.86,0:07:36.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Coco, hurry down the escape \Nroute with Byro-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.22,0:07:37.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.93,0:07:40.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no time to nitpick!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.07,0:07:43.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at how strong they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.64,0:07:47.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The outcome is as obvious \Nas vinegar melting papyrus!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.04,0:07:49.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Slow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.82,0:07:56.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A gale force wind from the \Nfore... becomes a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.10,0:08:02.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.13,0:08:05.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still something that I can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.20,0:08:10.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I was born a man, there's still \Nsomething I can do, even if it puts my life at risk!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.27,0:08:14.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You people!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:17.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You have something that doesn't \Nrightfully belong to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:20.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if there's a difference \Nin our strengths,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.61,0:08:22.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't take even one step back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.85,0:08:23.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.89,0:08:26.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He can be a decent person too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.15,0:08:27.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.92,0:08:31.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's pointless... \NDull-witted fellow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.43,0:08:30.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Hey! Are you listening to me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.12,0:08:33.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're... You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.11,0:08:37.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're my Rosslyn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.63,0:08:39.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.23,0:08:40.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:43.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Angel. And I hate men who act too familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.60,0:08:45.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Lightning bonus!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.60,0:08:45.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Love at first sight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.65,0:08:47.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll never be popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.58,0:08:51.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It made my whole body shudder. \NDefinitely a presentiment of romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.52,0:08:54.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm the one that zapped you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:08:58.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The difference in power \Nbetween us is obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.19,0:09:00.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasting time...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.21,0:09:03.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fairy Tail is weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:05.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.03,0:09:08.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Angel, get rid of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.31,0:09:09.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.14,0:09:11.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The cost is 30...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.71,0:09:15.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's Angel! The Celestial Wizard, Angel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.76,0:09:18.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I suspected as much, though it seems \Nlike she's got an odd personality!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.33,0:09:21.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maiden who walks with \Nthe Celestial Spirits...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.38,0:09:24.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was a child then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.02,0:09:27.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, as my name implies, I'm an angel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.96,0:09:30.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You think that Spirits can stand up against an angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.32,0:09:34.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you some beautiful Angel Magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.17,0:09:38.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But before that, people will \Ngrovel before me, despair...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.39,0:09:40.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...and sacrifice their own lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.20,0:09:45.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the power that comes \Nfrom the light in my own name!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:50.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I summon the angel that calls \Nforth victory... Barakiel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.15,0:09:57.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Protect the seal and seal \N{\i1}away{\i0} this burial ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.61,0:10:10.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.63,0:10:14.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No! What the blazes is goin' on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:18.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. My bad feeling \Nturned out to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:21.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were right? Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.97,0:10:26.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the result you predicted, Samuel?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.23,0:10:29.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My calculations were off-base... not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.92,0:10:33.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I only made it look like \Nmy calculations were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:36.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:38.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.50,0:10:39.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you feel it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.41,0:10:43.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The presence of evil, like \Nyou've never felt before...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:47.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are Byro-sama, Dan, and Coco?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.55,0:10:49.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.52,0:10:59.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oracion Seis? How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.17,0:11:02.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They should still be imprisoned!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.91,0:11:04.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.60,0:11:07.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So... who else is at the site?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.43,0:11:09.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.08,0:11:11.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fairy Tail wizards, for example...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.36,0:11:15.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fairy Tail again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.35,0:11:19.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, ever since that \Nguild got a new master,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:23.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe they've \Ncaused any major trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.45,0:11:25.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.01,0:11:27.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Makarov Dreyar has returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.60,0:11:31.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I've heard, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.95,0:11:34.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment he's back, this happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.03,0:11:38.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Org, what's funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:42.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. I thought this is just like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.79,0:11:44.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing to laugh about.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.56,0:11:49.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain of the Detention Corps is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.04,0:11:51.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Good timing. Let him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.03,0:11:57.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Lahar of the 4th Enforcement \Nand Detention Corps, at your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.33,0:12:00.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been waiting for you. Speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.80,0:12:03.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. I shall make my report.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.93,0:12:07.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by your expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.51,0:12:12.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the Oracion Seis that appeared in \Nthe desert is the genuine article.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.91,0:12:15.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am astonished at your \Ndiscerning eyes, Chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.39,0:12:16.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.57,0:12:19.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I regret to report
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.76,0:12:21.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that those who should be in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.35,0:12:26.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,namely, Midnight, Cobra, Angel, \Nand Racer, four of Oracion Seis,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.14,0:12:29.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,along with the one they later acted with,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.64,0:12:31.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,formerly of Eisenwald, Erigor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.39,0:12:36.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...have all escaped from confinement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.65,0:12:41.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Simulacra made from magic \Nwere in each of their cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.25,0:12:46.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,First him, then the Six Generals...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.30,0:12:49.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Simulation Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.63,0:12:52.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Though magic shouldn't have \Nworked in any of the cells...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.97,0:12:55.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We think they were helped by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.35,0:12:59.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They were imprisoned for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.39,0:13:02.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there someone who had \Ncontact with Oracion Seis?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.20,0:13:03.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. Just one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.78,0:13:08.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A priest sent over by the \Narchbishop of Zentopia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.53,0:13:12.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He came to visit them at certain \Nset times to take their confessions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.10,0:13:14.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and help them atone for their sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.53,0:13:16.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.79,0:13:19.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no record of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.91,0:13:22.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:26.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And even if there is no record, there \Nmust be surveillance lacrima, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.20,0:13:30.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There must still be footage of the priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.45,0:13:35.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The other day, all of the surveillance lacrima \Nin the prison were switched out at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.34,0:13:38.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so everything related \Nto this was disposed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.26,0:13:40.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow the disposal route.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.35,0:13:44.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Find the footage and verify \Nthe person's identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.81,0:13:47.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And Zentopia should be paid a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.17,0:13:50.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall meet with the archbishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.03,0:13:56.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment, our only clue is \Nthat priest. Tread carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.27,0:13:56.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:03.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.09,0:14:08.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu! You regained consciousness?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.03,0:14:11.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.30,0:14:12.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue Pegasus!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.23,0:14:14.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue Pegasus?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.44,0:14:19.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you remember my parfum?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.39,0:14:22.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me? Where's everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.65,0:14:24.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Worry not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:26.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all just sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.03,0:14:31.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No one is seriously injured, so we're \Nletting them rest up a bit. Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.05,0:14:33.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.03,0:14:37.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my! Natsu-kun is up, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.01,0:14:37.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.85,0:14:40.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez! How long were you gonna sleep?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.27,0:14:42.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You better give your thanks to them, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.10,0:14:44.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is incredible, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.54,0:14:48.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiya-san is the one who saved \Nus from under all that wreckage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:51.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really? Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.66,0:14:54.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're comrades who fought \Ntogether. I need no thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.21,0:14:57.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many good men here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.85,0:15:01.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a waste for them to \Nmix it up with the women.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.80,0:15:03.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:06.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking after you, Gray-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.75,0:15:08.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me "chan"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.54,0:15:10.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm grateful, Master Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.74,0:15:12.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You lied down next to him, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.45,0:15:15.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.65,0:15:17.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the glittery guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:22.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hibiki and the others are in another \Nland for a different matter. Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:24.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Leon?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:27.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiya dropped him off at Lamia Scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:28.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And Legion?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.08,0:15:31.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see anyone there but you folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.16,0:15:33.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.83,0:15:34.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.27,0:15:37.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those bastards... Dammit...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.70,0:15:39.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They were toying with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.35,0:15:42.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, we're gonna kick their asses!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.00,0:15:47.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have also heard of Oracion \NSeis's resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.44,0:15:48.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You have my support.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.77,0:15:49.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I can rely on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.52,0:15:53.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Michelle?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.24,0:15:56.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she was going out to get \Nsome fresh air a little while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.60,0:16:03.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.05,0:16:07.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought you that clock hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:09.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault, Michelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.29,0:16:13.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But so many people have gotten hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.50,0:16:15.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the problem just \Nkeeps getting bigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:17.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.39,0:16:20.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure we'll solve the problem. You'll see!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.25,0:16:23.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, even if
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.99,0:16:26.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the only good thing was being \Nable to meet you, I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.70,0:16:32.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame yourself! Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:35.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.47,0:16:40.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-san... I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.37,0:16:59.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Father... Why did you entrust \Nthat clock hand to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.55,0:17:02.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you were thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.16,0:17:07.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The same thing with "Key of the Starry \NHeavens"... What did you want to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.95,0:17:10.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I said... not to, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.10,0:17:14.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.10,0:17:16.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.47,0:17:19.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to try reading "Key of \Nthe Starry Heavens" one more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.23,0:17:24.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to try thinking one more time \Nabout what Father tried to tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.22,0:17:28.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you hate this book?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.60,0:17:30.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.75,0:17:34.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's making a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.44,0:17:39.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us, Asuka. What do you \Nmean, they're making a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.94,0:17:43.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they shouldn't collect the pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.24,0:17:45.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're talking about the clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.49,0:17:50.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! It says \Nright there in the book!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.08,0:17:56.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... We were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:17:58.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.75,0:18:01.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. Now I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.73,0:18:04.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It meant we mustn't collect them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.59,0:18:05.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.74,0:18:06.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.26,0:18:08.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.55,0:18:12.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We weren't supposed to collect them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.86,0:18:16.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the message in this book meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.75,0:18:19.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The pieces of the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.03,0:18:22.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We weren't supposed to get them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.32,0:18:25.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... don't tell me we...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.75,0:18:28.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...were doing the opposite?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.85,0:18:31.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what Angel was talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.62,0:18:34.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They were waiting for us to gather them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.50,0:18:36.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it seems...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.34,0:18:39.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That image was a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.48,0:18:45.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to figure it out and got cocky...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.66,0:18:47.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.15,0:18:49.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:51.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.00,0:18:55.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.98,0:18:58.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like the outcome was truly bitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.58,0:19:02.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bitter! I just know that \Nsomething bad is going to happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.46,0:19:04.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.59,0:19:09.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, your dad {\i1}did{\i0} beat around the bush...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.20,0:19:13.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right? He was roundabout \Nwith that anagram or whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.63,0:19:16.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At least it was too difficult \Nfor someone I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.87,0:19:20.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All he had to do was tell \Nus not to collect them!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.65,0:19:23.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some people who get a fever \Nfrom thinking about something too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.47,0:19:27.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe my magic powers up with that fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.33,0:19:29.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's give each other riddles!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.23,0:19:31.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Now I'm fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.89,0:19:36.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Is Lucy-san laughing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.95,0:19:40.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, after all, you're all weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.16,0:19:42.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What would be the point in brooding?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.25,0:19:44.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like they say, "Fortune \Ncomes in by a merry gate."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.19,0:19:45.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.44,0:19:47.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all trying to cheer me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.96,0:19:49.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You really think that's likely?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.45,0:19:51.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, it'll probably \Nrain tomorrow, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.94,0:19:54.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?! You lookin' for a fight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:55.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See, you were tryin' to cheer her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:57.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to fight, take it outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:20:01.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't fight, for my sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.01,0:20:02.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It ain't for your sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.66,0:20:05.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Fairy Tail I know and love...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.36,0:20:10.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone makes mistakes. \NBut then you recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:15.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at all of the friends \Nyou have here who adore you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.20,0:20:18.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be difficult for \Nanything to change that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:23.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep that in mind, you should be able \Nto get back on your feet any number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.07,0:20:24.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:32.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me enter, Your Holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.30,0:20:37.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have urgent news that must \Nreach the archbishop's ears!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.57,0:20:41.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid that I cannot \Nlet even you in, Duke Byro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.32,0:20:46.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, the only person who may have an \Naudience with the archbishop is me, Rapowant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.31,0:20:49.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall pass along your message.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.74,0:20:51.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Every second counts!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.39,0:20:55.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Infinity Clock was \Nstolen by Oracion Seis!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.45,0:20:56.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.65,0:20:59.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am well aware of that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.67,0:21:01.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lose your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.75,0:21:03.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How does he already know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.73,0:21:05.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.73,0:21:07.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cardinal Rapowant...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.41,0:21:12.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like his type. For one thing, \Nyou never know what he's thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.30,0:21:18.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the archbishop plucked him, an \Ninfluential person, from the local parish,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.48,0:21:21.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I just can't bring myself to trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.81,0:21:24.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What did His Grace say in response?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.60,0:21:29.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He gave Legion a new duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.02,0:21:40.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess! I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.01,0:21:45.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Coco... You betrayed Legion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.87,0:21:46.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Holiness!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.18,0:21:51.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, you turned your back on \Nthe faith while a member of Legion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.74,0:21:53.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you prepared to face the consequences?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:21:55.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.19,0:21:59.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no regrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.92,0:22:07.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That sound...!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.46,0:22:11.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Infinity Clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.93,0:22:13.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's ringin' out from somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.68,0:23:58.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what the "infinity" \Npart of the Infinity Clock is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.19,0:24:00.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we knew that, we wouldn't have \Ncome this far lookin' for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.85,0:24:02.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.67,0:24:04.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fish, it's a clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.08,0:24:07.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean. When the \Ndoors open, there's fish inside
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.10,0:24:11.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and no matter how many you take out, there \Nare more in there, so it's an Infinity Fish Clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.06,0:24:13.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When did it become a fish clock?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.80,0:24:16.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Hunt Down the Infinity Clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.47,0:24:18.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you think it is, Natsu?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.62,0:24:22.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the clock is another \Nclock and so on and so on!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.72,0:24:24.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That{\i0} part's infinite?!
